<!DOCTYPE document PUBLIC
  "-//Apache Software Foundation//DTD XDOC 1.0//EN"
  "http://maven.apache.org/dtd/xdoc_1_0.dtd">
<document>
  <properties>
    <title>How to install the poll component</title>
  </properties>
  <body>
    <section name="How to install the poll component">
      <subsection name="Prerequisites">
        <p>
          These instructions assume that you have a Hippo project based on the Hippo project archetype, i.e.
          a Maven multiproject consisting of at least three submodules: cms, site and content.
        </p>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Installation in CMS/Repository">
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>Add this dependencies to the pom.xml of your <i>cms</i> module:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.poll</groupId>
    <artifactId>poll-addon-repository</artifactId>
  </dependency>]]></source>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              Rebuild your project. After startup, you should have the availability
              of a standard Poll document type, plus a poll compound type to include
              a poll in your own document type.
            </p>
            <p><span class="note">Note:</span> on <strong>Hippo 7.8</strong> and later, be sure to use startup option <code>-Drepo.bootstrap=true</code>
              for initializing the types, see
              <a href="http://www.onehippo.org/7_8/library/concepts/content-repository/content-bootstrap.html">Content Bootstrap</a></p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Installation in HST site">
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>Add this dependency the pom.xml of your <i>site</i> module:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.onehippo.forge.poll</groupId>
    <artifactId>poll-hst-client</artifactId>
  </dependency>]]></source>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Add the poll content beans to the automatic bean scanning configuration in WEB-INF/web.xml:</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
<context-param>
  <param-name>hst-beans-annotated-classes</param-name>
  <param-value>
      ...
    classpath*:org/onehippo/forge/poll/contentbean/**/*.class
  </param-value>
</context-param>]]></source>
            <p>or, alternatively, add these beans in the HST file site/src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/beans-annotated-classes.xml</p>
            <source><![CDATA[
  <hst-content-beans>
    <annotated-class>
      org.onehippo.forge.poll.contentbean.PollDocument
    </annotated-class>
    <annotated-class>
      org.onehippo.forge.poll.contentbean.compound.Poll
    </annotated-class>
    <annotated-class>
      org.onehippo.forge.poll.contentbean.compound.Option
    </annotated-class>
  </hst-content-beans>]]></source>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </subsection>
    </section>
  </body>
</document>
